30/06/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police seized 129.3kg of heroin in an operation in eastern Turkey on Monday (June 29th), media reported.
Police officers detained three suspected drug traffickers in the operation in the town of Malatya and say the heroin was headed for Istanbul.
In only the past month, authorities seized more than 1 tonne of heroin across the country.
(Anadolu news agency, Haber Turk, Xinhua - 29/06/09)
